text.tspan: Prevalence of Polio Rates in the United States
The reported rates are per 100,000 US population and include both wild- and vaccine-derived type polio infections
that occurred indigenously and as imported cases.
Source: Our World In Data based on US Public Health Service; US Center for Disease Control; and WHO
